  "prompt": "What's the best way to calculate percentage off of something?",
  "response": "To calculate a percentage off, follow these steps:\n\n1. Original price: Start with the original price\n2. Discount percentage: Decide the percentage you want to take off\n3. Calculation method:\n   a) Multiply original price by the discount percentage\n   b) Divide that result by 100\n   c) Subtract that amount from the original price\n\nExample:\n- Original price: $50\n- Discount: 20% off\n- Calculation: \n  1. $50 \u00d7 20 = 1000\n  2. 1000 \u00f7 100 = $10 (discount amount)\n  3. $50 - $10 = $40 (final price)\n\nQuick shortcut:\n- Multiply original price by (1 - discount percentage/100)\n- Example: $50 \u00d7 (1 - 0.20) = $40\n\nMost calculators and smartphones have percentage functions that can help make this quick and easy.",
